{% extends 'BioPublicBundle:Content:instruction.html.twig' %}

{% block content %}
	<div>
		{% image 'bundles/biopublic/images/mainpage.png' output='images/*.png' %}
			<img src="{{ asset_url }}"/>
		{% endimage %}
		<h2> Welcome <i>{{app.user.username}}</i></h2>
		<p>From here you can control most aspects the site. Every function of the site is broken into logical groups on the sidebar. Go straight to the tools by clicking the appropriate <span class="leaf"><a style="display:inline;font-size:13px !important;">Link</a></span> on the sidebar. Or learn more about how to use each tool by selecting the <span class="branch"><a style="padding:0px;">title</a></span> above it.</p>

		{% if is_granted('ROLE_SUPER_ADMIN') %}
			<p>Only registered users who have been promoted to <i>ADMIN</i> and above can view these pages and make changes. If you are a <i>SUPER ADMIN</i> you can manage various users <i>roles</i> through the <a href="{{ path('view_users') }}">Users</a> page.</p>
		{% endif %}

		<p style="margin-bottom:0px;">After making an edit to the site you'll usually come across a colored bar on the top of your page (examples shown at bottom of the page). If the operation was a success the bar will be green. If the operation failed for some reason it will be red with a descriptive message of what went wrong. If the error was due to an improperly filled out form, the offending entry will appear</p>
		<div id="form" style="margin-top:0px;">
			<div class="error row-error" data-tip="error message goes here" style="margin-top:12px;"><label>like this:</label><input></div>
			<div></div>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div>
		<div class="success">
			This means that the operation was a success!
		</div>
		<div class="failure">
			The operation failed. You should fix the problem and try again.
		</div>
	</div>
{% endblock %}